Class MyCalendar

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Calendar
      • java.util.GregorianCalendar
        • MyCalendar
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.util.Calendar>

    public class MyCalendar
extends java.util.GregorianCalendar
    Represents a Calendar that can hold events and print them to console in either a day or month view, print all events as a list, delete all events from a particular day or delete all events in Calendar.
    See Also:

      • getDayView

        public void getDayView(java.util.Date date)
        Prints Day View of the Calendar for a given date. It first prints date and then all the events scheduled for this date.
        Parameters:
        date - date for which to show Day View

      • getMonthView

        public void getMonthView()
        Prints Month View of Calendar by calling helper method to print current month to console highlighting days with scheduled events.

      • getMonthView

        public void getMonthView(boolean highlight_today)
        Prints Month View of Calendar by calling the helper method to print current month to console with today's date highlighted.
        Parameters:
        highlight_today - if true, today's date is highlighted; otherwise, today's date is not highlighted
